OL,3,CHigher than expected jump in inflation
OL,4,Cto 3% may not be as bad as it looks
OL,6,FThis pair of unusual features -
OL,7,Fairfares and school fees - means the
OL,8,FBank of England may be less likely to
OL,9,Fhold interest rates higher for longer
OL,10,Fas a result of Wednesday's CPI.
OL,12,FBut let's not get too excited;
OL,13,Finflation is still expected to rise
OL,14,Fthis year (to 3.7% thinks the Bank),
OL,15,Fgrowth is still poor to non-existent
OL,16,Fand we have yet to feel the full
OL,17,Feffects of the chancellor's hike to
OL,18,Femployer national insurance.
OL,20,FSo even if it's not as bad as it looks
OL,21,Ftoday, it's still pretty bad.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/5
